import pickle
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline

# load previous dataframe
with open ('df_target_all.pickle','rb') as f:
    target_all = pickle.load(f)
    
with open ('sarima_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug.pickle','rb') as f:
    sarima_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug = pickle.load(f)

with open ('prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug.pickle','rb') as f:
    prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug = pickle.load(f)

prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug = prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug.rename(columns={'Predicted Monthly Sale':'Prophet Prediction'})
prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug['Prophet Prediction'] = round(prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug['Prophet Prediction'],0)

idx = prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug.index
idx = idx.shift(1, freq ='D') # shifting the index by 5 days 

prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug.set_index(idx, inplace=True) # reset index with shifted dates
prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug

# plot the predicted 12 months sales (out of time)
ax = target_all.plot(label='Observed', figsize=(14,5))
sarima_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug.plot(ax=ax, label='SARIMA Prediction')
prophet_sales_2019_Sep_2020_Aug.plot(ax=ax, label='Prophet Prediction')

ax.set_xlabel('Date')
ax.set_ylabel('Monthly Revenue Collected From Target Stores')

plt.title('Target Monthly Sales Comparison: SARIMA vs Prophet')
plt.legend()

plt.savefig('Target Monthly Sales Comparison: SARIMA vs Prophet.png', format='png',dpi=300)
